In mathematics, '''Gottlieb polynomials''' are a family of discrete [[orthogonal polynomials]] introduced by {{harvs|txt|first=Morris J.|last=Gottlieb|year=1938}}. They are given by

:<math>\displaystyle \ell_n(x,\lambda) = e^{-n\lambda}\sum_k(1-e^\lambda)^k\binom{n}{k}\binom{x}{k} =e^{-n\lambda}{}_2F_1(-n,-x;1;1-e^\lambda)</math>

