In mathematics, '''Meixner polynomials''' (also called '''discrete Laguerre polynomials''') are a family of [[discrete orthogonal polynomials]] introduced by {{harvs|txt|authorlink=Josef Meixner|first=Josef|last= Meixner|year=1934}}. They are given in terms of [[binomial coefficient]]s and the (rising) [[Pochhammer symbol]] by
:<math>M_n(x,\beta,\gamma) = \sum_{k=0}^n (-1)^k{n \choose k}{x\choose k}k!(x+\beta)_{n-k}\gamma^{-k}</math>

